Sign up to our Next Africa newsletter and  follow Bloomberg Africa on Twitter South Africa’s main stock index climbs 0.4% as of 11:40 a.m. in Johannesburg. The benchmark index has advanced 4.3% this week, and is set for the strongest performance since early June. Global luxury retailer and market heavyweight Richemont is the biggest contributors to the gains, surging 2.7% on Friday after a 5.9% jump in the previous session. Richemont has attracted some M&A speculation in the wake of the collapse of LVMH’s proposed acquisition of Tiffany.